    "attributes": {
        "action": "Fund free TV for all patients in NHS hospitals. ",
        "additional_details": "Luckily I was able to afford paying it (despite the unfairness) but I was the only person on my ward to be watching because the other patients weren't in a position to pay for 1 reason or another, how can it be right that when people are vulnerable they are able to be exorbitantly charged for something that is free (as long as you have a licence, which is a fraction of the cost of this system) at home at home",
        "background": "After a recent stay in hospital it cost me \u00a315.80 to watch tv for 2 days, which is wholly unfair if not extortionate. I would like you to debate banning this charge for channels that are free elsewhere.\r\n \r\n",
